The paper proposes a method for writing and checking specifications using behaviors and equivalence theories, which are common topics in the sub-fields of logic (cs.LO) and software engineering (cs.SE). The use of a satisfiability modulo theory solver (SMT solver) suggests a focus on programming languages (cs.PL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the hierarchical construction of vocabularies may also relate to formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL).
